Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @potatoes{12%oz} into 1⁄4-inch-thick rounds. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> Trim green beans if necessary. Swap in green beans for potatoes; roast until browned
> and tender, 10-12 minutes. (Save potatoes for another use.)

While potatoes roast, halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}. Halve @potato buns{2}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp}, @ketchup{1}, @ancho chili powder{1%tsp},
@beef stock concentrate{1}, half the @cornstarch{1%tbsp}, and @water{1%tbsp}. (For 4
servings, use all the cornstarch and 2 TBSP water.) Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook,
stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Add BBQ sauce mixture to pan with beef. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and
beef is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off
heat.

While filling cooks, toast buns until golden brown.

Fill buns with as much beef filling and @sliced dill pickles{1} as you like. Divide sloppy
joes between plates. Serve with potatoes and any remaining pickle on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.